data.name: I amtechno w/ FRANCOIS X (FR)

eventdata.description:
Line-up:

☐ FRANCOIS X (CONCRETE, FR) 
☐ MAARTEN MITTENDORFF & JASPER WOLFF
☐ JEAN PIERRE ENFANT
☐ KEITH CARNAL
☐ LA VONDEL
☐ SJEROEM
☐ VERDI

Na een succesvolle eerste editie op 17 januari met Roman Lindau keert    Iamtechno terug naar Studio 80!
Wij hebben de eer om één van Frankrijks grootste Techno Dj’s voor het eerst naar Amsterdam te halen.
De Parijzenaar heeft in vele steden en de grootste clubs van Europa gedraaid, hoog tijd om hem aan Amsterdam voor te stellen dus. 
Voor deze editie hebben we niemand minder dan Francois X!

Francois X is een onmiskenbare personage in de opkomende techno scene in Parijs. Francois X bewijst zich als DJ, producer én label eigenaar en staat garant voor kwaliteit. Als medeoprichter van het platenlabel en productiebedrijf Dement3d krijgt hij steeds meer internationale bekendheid.

Door zijn uitzonderlijke sets heeft Francois X residentie in Concrete (Parijs) en sluit hij regelmatig af in toonaangevende clubs als Berghain.

Samen met Maarten Mittendorff & Jasper Wolff en onze residents Keith Carnal en La Vondel, zal Francois X de muzikale invulling van de avond verzorgen.

De tweede zaal wordt gehost door “De Beat Industrie”. De jonge organisatie uit Haarlem timmert al geruime tijd aan de weg en hosten regelmatig succesvolle avonden in hun natuurlijke habitat. 
Voor Studio80 hebben De Beat Industrie de frisse geluiden van Verdi & Sjoerem en van special guest Jan Pierre Enfant, bekend van zijn residentie in Trouw.

data.name: THE GREAT ESCAPE - DETROIT SWINDLE ALBUM RELEASE

eventdata.description:
The two swindlers Maarten & Lars -aka Detroit Swindle- have been partners in crime for a while now, making dope beats, breaking down dance floors all over the world and simply leaving everyone caught with their pants down, figuring out what the hell just happened.

With the release of their debut album, they’re definitely pulling off their biggest heist to date. With the album conspiracy completely set up, all they had to focus on was to lay low and plan their clean getaway. So as we speak, the two most elusive swindlers in electronic music are plotting their next move and calling it: The Great Escape.

Detroit Swindle need the support of their favourite henchmen to keep their scheme going, so take a leap of faith and join them now in their Great Escape.

Catch the escapees at Studio 80 on the 29th of March for the release party of their upcoming debut album ‘Boxed Out’.

data.name: TOMORROW IS NOW, KID! w/ JOVONN (USA)

eventdata.description:
Jovonn is an artist who burst onto the top 10 billboard R'n'B charts in 1990 and has never taken his foot off the pedal. Though his debut showed him as a producer, songwriter and singer in one neat package, rather it would be in the smokey mists of damp, sweaty underground clubs that this innate multi-talented musician would feel fulfilled. His love for house music and the collecting of dance records, had him choose a route for himself that some would call daring, considering he could have become one of the biggest R'n'B names of his time, as Bobby Brown or Boyz II Men. 

In the years following, Jovonn produced many R'n'B artists, remixed a lot of huge names (such as Mary J. Blidge, Chaka Khan amongst others), and set up and developed his own label Goldtone. Boasting an amazing three page long curriculum of music production on reference website Discogs.com, Jovonn is as much a real underground legend as they come, and no house head can have a clean conscience if they miss out on this master's performance during the next Tomorrow Is Now, Kid! party.

Fresh kid on the block, Moody Mehran has the honor of warming up the night, while our very own Daan Groeneveld will close the night back 2 back with Alex Salvador.

In the ever-cozy back room we've invited Makcim and Daniele Temperilli, who's steady and edgy grooves provide an alternative vibe for the floor. 

Come down to Studio 80 on Friday March 14th, to enjoy a full night of dancing... in the dark... where the real underground is.

FRIDAY MARCH 14TH
Studio 80 - Rembrandtplein 17
23:00 - 05:00

Tickets available here: http://bit.ly/1i8AXnG

Resident Advisor: http://bit.ly/tink14m-ra
